# TypeScript Standards

## Strict Mode

TypeScript strict mode is enabled. Follow these rules:

- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow with type guards
- Always type function parameters and return types for exported functions
- Use `import type` for type-only imports

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — swallowing errors
try { await fetchData(); } catch (e) {}

// ✅ GOOD — log and rethrow or handle
try {
  await fetchData();
} catch (error) {
  console.error('Failed to fetch data:', error);
  throw error;
}
```

## Path Aliases

```typescript
// Use path aliases (configured in tsconfig.json)
import { something } from '@/core/domain';        // → ./src/core/domain
import { Component } from '@/components/ui/Button'; // → ./components/ui/Button
import { util } from '@tinadmin/core';              // → workspace package
```

## Async/Await

- Prefer `async/await` over `.then()` chains
- Always handle promise rejections
- Use `Promise.all()` for independent concurrent operations
